{"id":"PROP-W5B14-3","text":"The RANDOM_CHALLENGE_KZG_CELL_BATCH_DOMAIN separator used in compute_verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_challenge (SG-006) MUST be unique to this specific batch verification context and MUST NOT collide with domain separators used in any other protocol or verification context.","type":"invariant","source_assumption_id":"asm-003","source_invariant_id":"SG-006:INV-002","source_threat_id":"stride-023","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-006:compute_verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_challenge","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-008"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"A cross-protocol attack: if the domain separator collides with another protocol's domain, an attacker could construct a valid proof for one context and replay it in this context."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Domain separator collision could allow cross-protocol proof replay attacks, accepting proofs from unrelated contexts as valid batch KZG cell proofs.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires demonstrating a collision with another protocol's domain separator and a cross-context proof acceptance."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-4","text":"The hash input order in compute_verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_challenge (SG-006) MUST be deterministic and canonical across all implementations. Two honest nodes receiving the same (commitments, cell_indices, cosets_evals, proofs) MUST compute the same challenge r.","type":"invariant","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-006:INV-003","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-006:compute_verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_challenge","nodes":["actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-008"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"Non-deterministic hash ordering would cause different nodes to compute different challenges, leading to inconsistent verification results and potential consensus splits."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"CRITICAL","severity_justification":"Non-deterministic Fiat-Shamir challenge computation would cause consensus splits: some nodes accept a proof while others reject it, partitioning the network.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC demonstrating inconsistent verification results across two implementations due to ordering differences."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-5","text":"The universal verification equation in verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_impl (SG-015) MUST satisfy: e(LL, LR) == e(RL, [1]) where LL = g1_lincomb(proofs, r_powers), LR = KZG_SETUP_G2_MONOMIAL[n], and RL = RLC - RLI + RLP. A valid set of cells and proofs MUST always pass this check; an invalid set MUST fail with overwhelming probability (1 - 1/p).","type":"invariant","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-015:INV-001","source_threat_id":"stride-020","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-015:verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_impl","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation","Length checks","Range checks"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"Attacker sends crafted data column sidecars. The verification equation is the final cryptographic gate. If the random challenge r has insufficient entropy or the equation is incorrectly implemented, invalid proofs could pass."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"CRITICAL","severity_justification":"Bypassing the verification equation allows an attacker to inject invalid cells that pass verification, breaking data availability guarantees across the entire network.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC demonstrating acceptance of an invalid cell-proof pair by the batch verifier."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-6","text":"In verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_impl (SG-015), the random challenge r MUST bind all inputs via Fiat-Shamir. The challenge MUST have full entropy of the BLS scalar field (approximately 2^255 bits). hash_to_bls_field MUST produce a uniformly random BLS field element.","type":"invariant","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-015:INV-002","source_threat_id":"stride-020","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-015:verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_impl","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002","tb-008"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"If the challenge r has insufficient entropy (e.g., due to weak hash or truncation), an attacker can find inputs where individual proofs are invalid but the aggregated verification equation holds."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"CRITICAL","severity_justification":"Insufficient entropy in the random challenge directly enables proof forgery in the batch verification scheme, a network-wide consensus failure.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires analysis of hash_to_bls_field output distribution and PoC showing bias exploitation."}

