{"id":"PROP-W5B14-7","text":"The commitments list passed to verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_impl (SG-015) MUST contain no duplicates. Commitment deduplication in verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch (SG-021) MUST use byte-exact comparison, not hash-based comparison, to avoid hash collision attacks.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":"asm-013","source_invariant_id":"SG-015:INV-003","source_threat_id":"stride-005","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-021:verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation","Byte length checks"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"An attacker provides commitment_bytes over P2P. If deduplication uses a weak hash, the attacker could craft two semantically different commitments that map to the same deduplicated index, causing weight aggregation errors in the verification equation."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Incorrect deduplication causes the random linear combination weights to be wrong, potentially accepting invalid proofs or rejecting valid ones.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC with crafted commitment bytes that trigger deduplication errors leading to incorrect verification results."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-8","text":"All commitment_indices in verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_impl (SG-015) MUST reference valid entries in the deduplicated commitments array, i.e., forall k: commitment_indices[k] < len(commitments).","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-015:INV-004","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-015:verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_impl","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation","Length checks"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"Out-of-bounds commitment_indices would cause array index out-of-bounds access, potentially crashing the node."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Out-of-bounds array access could crash the validator node, causing single-node DoS.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC demonstrating node crash via crafted commitment_indices."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-9","text":"In verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch (SG-021), all four input lists (commitment_bytes, cell_indices, cells, proofs_bytes) MUST have equal length. Mismatched lengths MUST cause the function to reject the input before any cryptographic operations.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-021:INV-002","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-021:verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"Mismatched array lengths from P2P input could cause out-of-bounds access or incorrect verification. This is the first validation checkpoint."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Bypassing length validation could lead to out-of-bounds memory access or incorrect cryptographic results, potentially crashing the node.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC showing crash or incorrect verification result from mismatched input lengths."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-10","text":"In verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch (SG-021), each cell_index MUST be strictly less than CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB. Out-of-range cell_indices MUST be rejected before being used in coset_for_cell or coset_shift_for_cell.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-021:INV-004","source_threat_id":"stride-017","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-021:verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"Attacker sends cell_indices >= CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB via P2P. coset_shift_for_cell and coset_for_cell access roots_brp[FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_CELL * cell_index], which would be out-of-bounds."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Out-of-bounds array access in coset_shift_for_cell or coset_for_cell could crash the node (segfault) or cause memory corruption, leading to single-node DoS.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC demonstrating node crash from out-of-range cell_index in P2P data column sidecar."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-11","text":"In verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch (SG-021), each commitment_bytes MUST have length exactly BYTES_PER_COMMITMENT, each cell MUST have length exactly BYTES_PER_CELL, and each proof_bytes MUST have length exactly BYTES_PER_PROOF. Incorrect lengths MUST be rejected.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-021:INV-001","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-021:verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"Incorrect byte lengths from P2P could cause deserialization errors, buffer overflows, or incorrect field element parsing."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Accepting incorrectly-sized bytes could cause buffer overflows or incorrect deserialization, potentially leading to crashes or memory corruption.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC demonstrating crash or unexpected behavior from malformed byte lengths."}

