{"id":"PROP-W5B14-12","text":"bytes_to_kzg_commitment and bytes_to_kzg_proof MUST perform BLS12-381 G1 subgroup checks during deserialization. Points not on the correct subgroup MUST be rejected. Accepting non-subgroup points would cause the pairing check to produce incorrect results.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":null,"source_threat_id":"stride-024","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-021:verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation","Byte length checks"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"An attacker provides commitment or proof bytes that deserialize to a point on the BLS12-381 curve but NOT in the correct G1 subgroup. Without subgroup checks, the pairing equation could give incorrect results."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"CRITICAL","severity_justification":"Missing subgroup checks in pairing-based cryptography is a well-known class of vulnerability. It allows forging proofs that pass the pairing check, breaking data availability guarantees.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC with a non-subgroup point that causes the pairing check to accept an invalid proof."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-13","text":"In verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch (SG-021), commitment deduplication MUST preserve semantic equivalence: forall k: deduplicated_commitments[commitment_indices[k]] == original_commitment_bytes[k]. The mapping from original indices to deduplicated indices MUST be bijective on equivalence classes.","type":"invariant","source_assumption_id":"asm-013","source_invariant_id":"SG-021:INV-003","source_threat_id":"stride-005","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-021:verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation","Byte length checks"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"An off-by-one in the commitment_indices mapping would cause weights to be accumulated against the wrong commitment in the verification equation."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Incorrect commitment-to-index mapping causes verification to aggregate weights incorrectly, potentially accepting invalid proofs.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC demonstrating a batch with deliberately structured commitments that exploit an off-by-one in the mapping."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-14","text":"recover_cells_and_kzg_proofs (SG-024) MUST require at least CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB / 2 cells for recovery. If fewer than 50% of cells are provided, the function MUST reject the input. This threshold is mathematically required by the rate-2 Reed-Solomon erasure coding.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":"asm-004","source_invariant_id":"SG-024:INV-002","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-024:recover_cells_and_kzg_proofs","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-003"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation","Cell count check"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"An attacker withholds cells so that fewer than 50% are available. If the threshold check is bypassed, recovery produces an incorrect polynomial."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Bypassing the 50% threshold produces a mathematically incorrect recovered polynomial, which then generates incorrect cells and proofs that propagate through the network.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC showing recovery with fewer than 50% cells produces incorrect output that is accepted downstream."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-15","text":"In recover_cells_and_kzg_proofs (SG-024), cell_indices MUST be unique and in ascending sorted order. Duplicate cell_indices MUST be rejected. forall i < j: cell_indices[i] < cell_indices[j].","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-024:INV-003","source_threat_id":"stride-019","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-024:recover_cells_and_kzg_proofs","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-003"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"An attacker provides duplicate cell_indices with conflicting cell data. If uniqueness is not enforced, polynomial interpolation produces incorrect results, and the recovered polynomial differs from the original."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Duplicate cell_indices with conflicting cell data would cause polynomial recovery to produce an incorrect polynomial, leading to distribution of invalid data.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC with duplicate cell_indices and conflicting cells causing incorrect recovery."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-16","text":"In recover_cells_and_kzg_proofs (SG-024), all cell_indices MUST be in [0, CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB). Out-of-range indices MUST be rejected before polynomial recovery begins.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-024:INV-004","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-024:recover_cells_and_kzg_proofs","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-003"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"Out-of-range cell indices would cause out-of-bounds access in coset computation functions."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Out-of-bounds cell indices cause crashes in coset_for_cell and related functions, leading to single-node DoS.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC demonstrating node crash from out-of-range cell_index during recovery."}

