{"id":"PROP-W5B14-17","text":"After recover_polynomialcoeff (SG-023) produces a recovered polynomial, the caller MUST verify the recovered cells and proofs against the original KZG commitment. The recovery function itself does NOT verify commitment consistency. forall recovered_cell: verify_cell_kzg_proof(original_commitment, cell_index, recovered_cell, recovered_proof) == True.","type":"post-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":null,"source_threat_id":"stride-004","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-024:recover_cells_and_kzg_proofs","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-003"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation","Cell availability check"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"An attacker provides corrupted cells for valid cell_indices. Without post-recovery commitment verification, the node propagates incorrect data to other peers."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Missing post-recovery verification turns a validator node into a vector for distributing invalid data. Other nodes trusting reconstructed data accept corrupted cells.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC showing a node distributing corrupted cells after recovery from attacker-provided data without commitment re-verification."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-18","text":"The recovered polynomial from recover_polynomialcoeff (SG-023) MUST have degree strictly less than FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_BLOB. The output poly_coeff[:FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_BLOB] truncation MUST not discard any non-zero coefficients above FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_BLOB.","type":"post-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-023:INV-003","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-023:recover_polynomialcoeff","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-003"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["Cell availability check","50% threshold check"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"If the recovered polynomial has degree >= FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_BLOB, the truncation discards non-zero coefficients, producing an incorrect polynomial."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"MEDIUM","severity_justification":"Incorrect truncation produces wrong cells and proofs. However, this should be caught by post-recovery commitment verification.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires demonstrating crafted cell data that causes the recovered polynomial to exceed the expected degree."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-19","text":"In recover_polynomialcoeff (SG-023), the element-wise division reconstructed[i] = ez_over_coset[i] / zp_over_coset[i] MUST NOT encounter division by zero. The vanishing polynomial Z(x) evaluated on the coset (shifted by PRIMITIVE_ROOT_OF_UNITY) MUST be non-zero at every point. forall i: zp_over_coset[i] != 0.","type":"invariant","source_assumption_id":"asm-008","source_invariant_id":"SG-023:INV-002","source_threat_id":"stride-016","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-023:recover_polynomialcoeff","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-003"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["Cell availability check","50% threshold check"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"The coset shift by PRIMITIVE_ROOT_OF_UNITY ensures Z(x) has no roots on the coset. If the shift is incorrect, division by zero crashes the node."},"exploitability":"internal-bug","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Division by zero during recovery crashes the validator node. Although the root cause is an incorrect coset shift (implementation bug), the trigger is attacker-controlled cell withholding.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC demonstrating a division-by-zero crash during cell recovery triggered by specific missing cell patterns."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-20","text":"The coset_fft_field (SG-005) shift_factor MUST equal PRIMITIVE_ROOT_OF_UNITY. An incorrect shift factor would cause the coset to coincide with roots of vanishing polynomials, enabling division by zero in recover_polynomialcoeff.","type":"invariant","source_assumption_id":"asm-008","source_invariant_id":"SG-005:INV-001","source_threat_id":"stride-016","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-005:coset_fft_field","nodes":["actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-003"],"is_boundary_edge":false},"reachability":{"classification":"internal-only","entry_points":["Internal"],"attacker_controlled":false,"validation_layers":[],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"This is a constant correctness property. An incorrect PRIMITIVE_ROOT_OF_UNITY would be a fundamental implementation bug affecting all coset-based operations."},"exploitability":"internal-bug","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Incorrect shift factor causes systematic division-by-zero in all recovery operations, affecting every node running the incorrect implementation.","bug_bounty_eligible":false,"bug_bounty_notes":null}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-21","text":"The bit-reversal permutation applied in polynomial_eval_to_coeff (SG-007), coset_for_cell (SG-017), and coset_shift_for_cell (SG-016) MUST correctly map between evaluation-domain ordering and the canonical ordering expected by FFT. forall i: brp(brp(i)) == i (involution property).","type":"invariant","source_assumption_id":"asm-005","source_invariant_id":"SG-007:INV-002","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-007:polynomial_eval_to_coeff","nodes":["actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-001","tb-002","tb-003"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["Transaction","P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["Blob validation","Cell validation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"An incorrect bit-reversal permutation would produce wrong polynomial coefficients, leading to incorrect cells and proofs. This affects all blob processing and cell verification paths."},"exploitability":"internal-bug","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Incorrect permutation corrupts all polynomial conversions, producing incorrect proofs and cells that may or may not pass verification depending on the specific error.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires demonstrating a permutation implementation that produces incorrect polynomial coefficients."}

