{"id":"PROP-W5B14-22","text":"In divide_polynomialcoeff (SG-010), the divisor polynomial b MUST NOT be the zero polynomial, and its leading coefficient b[bpos] MUST be nonzero. Division by zero polynomial MUST be rejected.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":"asm-007","source_invariant_id":"SG-010:INV-001","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-010:divide_polynomialcoeff","nodes":["actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-003"],"is_boundary_edge":false},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["Cell availability check","50% threshold"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"The divisor polynomial is the vanishing polynomial constructed from missing cell roots. If all cells are present (no missing roots), the vanishing polynomial is the constant 1, which is valid. However, edge cases in construction could produce a zero polynomial."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Division by zero polynomial crashes the node during proof generation or polynomial recovery.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC showing a set of missing cell indices that produces a zero vanishing polynomial."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-23","text":"In interpolate_polynomialcoeff (SG-011), all xs values MUST be distinct. forall i != j: xs[i] != xs[j]. Duplicate xs values would cause (xs[i] - xs[j]).inverse() to attempt inverting zero, resulting in a crash.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":"asm-011","source_invariant_id":"SG-011:INV-001","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-011:interpolate_polynomialcoeff","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002","tb-003"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["Cell index validation","Coset computation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"The xs values are coset points derived from cell_indices. If duplicate cell_indices slip through validation, duplicate coset points would be passed to interpolation, causing a crash."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Division by zero in Lagrange interpolation crashes the validator node, causing single-node DoS.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC showing a crash in interpolation triggered by duplicate cell_indices that bypass validation."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-24","text":"In multiply_polynomialcoeff (SG-009), len(a) + len(b) MUST be <= FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_EXT_BLOB. This prevents the product polynomial from exceeding the extended evaluation domain, which would cause incorrect FFT results.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":"asm-010","source_invariant_id":"SG-009:INV-001","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-009:multiply_polynomialcoeff","nodes":["actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-001","tb-003"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["Transaction","P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["Blob size check","Cell count check"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"The assertion prevents buffer overflow during polynomial multiplication. If many cells are missing (close to 50%), the vanishing polynomial can be large, and the product with another polynomial could exceed bounds."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"MEDIUM","severity_justification":"Assertion bypass causes buffer overflow or incorrect polynomial arithmetic. Impact depends on memory safety of the implementation language.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC demonstrating assertion bypass with specific missing cell patterns."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-25","text":"In coset_shift_for_cell (SG-016), cell_index MUST be in [0, CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB). The assertion MUST be enforced before computing roots_brp[FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_CELL * cell_index].","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-016:INV-001","source_threat_id":"stride-017","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-016:coset_shift_for_cell","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"Attacker-controlled cell_index from P2P input. FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_CELL * cell_index could overflow or exceed array bounds."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Out-of-bounds array access crashes the node or causes memory corruption.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC showing node crash from crafted cell_index."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-26","text":"In coset_for_cell (SG-017), cell_index MUST be in [0, CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB), and the returned Coset MUST have exactly FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_CELL elements. The slice roots_brp[start : start + FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_CELL] MUST be in bounds.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-017:INV-001","source_threat_id":"stride-017","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-017:coset_for_cell","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["P2P gossip validation"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"Same as PROP-0025 but for the full coset retrieval."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Out-of-bounds slice access causes crashes or returns incorrect coset elements.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Same as PROP-0025."}

