{"id":"PROP-W5B14-27","text":"cell_to_coset_evals (SG-001) MUST produce a CosetEvals with exactly FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_CELL elements. Each cell byte segment [i*BYTES_PER_FIELD_ELEMENT : (i+1)*BYTES_PER_FIELD_ELEMENT] MUST be exactly BYTES_PER_FIELD_ELEMENT bytes.","type":"invariant","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-001:INV-001","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-001:cell_to_coset_evals","nodes":["actor-p2p-peer","actor-validator-node"],"edges":["tb-002"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["P2P"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["Cell byte length check"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"Cells received via P2P are deserialized. If the cell is shorter than expected, byte slicing produces undersized field element bytes."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"MEDIUM","severity_justification":"Incorrect field element count produces wrong coset evaluations, potentially causing verification errors.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC with malformed cell bytes."}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-28","text":"coset_evals_to_cell (SG-002) is the exact inverse of cell_to_coset_evals (SG-001) for valid field elements. forall valid cell: coset_evals_to_cell(cell_to_coset_evals(cell)) == cell.","type":"invariant","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-002:INV-002","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-002:coset_evals_to_cell","nodes":["actor-validator-node"],"edges":[],"is_boundary_edge":false},"reachability":{"classification":"internal-only","entry_points":["Internal"],"attacker_controlled":false,"validation_layers":[],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"Roundtrip property. If violated, recovered cells differ from originals even with correct polynomial."},"exploitability":"internal-bug","severity":"MEDIUM","severity_justification":"Broken roundtrip causes recovered cells to differ from originals, producing invalid sidecars.","bug_bounty_eligible":false,"bug_bounty_notes":null}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-29","text":"The _fft_field (SG-003) MUST require len(vals) to be a power of 2 and len(vals) == len(roots_of_unity). Non-power-of-2 inputs MUST be rejected.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-003:INV-001","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-003:_fft_field","nodes":["actor-validator-node"],"edges":[],"is_boundary_edge":false},"reachability":{"classification":"internal-only","entry_points":["Internal"],"attacker_controlled":false,"validation_layers":[],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"FFT requires power-of-2 sizes for correctness. Non-power-of-2 sizes cause incorrect butterfly operations."},"exploitability":"internal-bug","severity":"MEDIUM","severity_justification":"Incorrect FFT results propagate to all polynomial operations, producing wrong cells and proofs.","bug_bounty_eligible":false,"bug_bounty_notes":null}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-30","text":"fft_field (SG-004) inverse FFT MUST correctly apply the normalization factor 1/N: forall polynomial p: ifft(fft(p)) == p. The inverse FFT MUST reverse the roots_of_unity order (except the first element).","type":"invariant","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-004:INV-001","source_threat_id":null,"covers":{"primary_element":"SG-004:fft_field","nodes":["actor-validator-node"],"edges":[],"is_boundary_edge":false},"reachability":{"classification":"internal-only","entry_points":["Internal"],"attacker_controlled":false,"validation_layers":[],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"The inverse FFT is used in polynomial_eval_to_coeff and recover_polynomialcoeff. Incorrect normalization produces wrong coefficients."},"exploitability":"internal-bug","severity":"HIGH","severity_justification":"Incorrect FFT normalization corrupts all polynomial coefficient computations, affecting proofs and recovery.","bug_bounty_eligible":false,"bug_bounty_notes":null}
{"id":"PROP-W5B14-31","text":"compute_cells_and_kzg_proofs (SG-020) MUST accept only blobs of exactly BYTES_PER_BLOB bytes. The output MUST contain exactly CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB cells and CELLS_PER_EXT_BLOB proofs.","type":"pre-condition","source_assumption_id":null,"source_invariant_id":"SG-020:INV-002","source_threat_id":"stride-014","covers":{"primary_element":"SG-020:compute_cells_and_kzg_proofs","nodes":["actor-blob-submitter","actor-block-proposer"],"edges":["tb-001"],"is_boundary_edge":true},"reachability":{"classification":"external-reachable","entry_points":["Transaction"],"attacker_controlled":true,"validation_layers":["Transaction validation","Blob size check"],"bug_bounty_scope":"in-scope","notes":"A blob submitter provides blob bytes via type-3 transaction. Incorrect blob size must be rejected before polynomial operations."},"exploitability":"external-attack","severity":"MEDIUM","severity_justification":"Incorrect blob sizes cause incorrect polynomial representations, but should be caught by earlier transaction validation.","bug_bounty_eligible":true,"bug_bounty_notes":"Requires PoC with a blob that bypasses size validation."}

